  "prompt": "What are some animals native to New Zealand?",
  "response": "New Zealand is home to a variety of unique and distinctive animals, many of which are not found anywhere else in the world. Some notable native species include:\n\n1. **Kiwi** - A flightless bird and a national icon of New Zealand, known for its long beak and small size.\n2. **Kea** - A large, intelligent parrot that is known for its playful nature and curiosity.\n3. **Takahe** - A large, flightless bird that was once thought to be extinct; it is a conservation success story.\n4. **K\u0101k\u0101p\u014d** - A critically endangered, nocturnal parrot that is also flightless.\n5. **P\u016bteke (Australasian bittern)** - A large, secretive marsh bird that has a distinctive booming call.\n6. **Hectors Dolphin** - One of the smallest dolphin species in the world, found only in New Zealand waters.\n7. **New Zealand Falcon (K\u0101rearea)** - A native raptor known for its agility and speed in flight.\n8. **W\u0113t\u0101** - A large insect that comes in various species; some can be quite large and are often compared to crickets.\n9. **Tuatara** - An ancient reptile that resembles a lizard and has a lineage dating back to the time of the dinosaurs.\n10. **Eel (Inanga)** - Eels in New Zealand are known for their long migrations and can grow quite large, with the longfin eel being particularly notable.\n\nThese animals reflect the diverse ecosystems and unique evolutionary history of New Zealand. Many of these species are threatened or endangered, and conservation efforts are ongoing to protect them.",
